--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages iftop.

iftop does for network usage what top does for CPU usage. It listens to network
traffic on a named interface and displays a table of current bandwidth usage by
pairs of hosts.
Handy for answering the question "why is our ADSL link so slow?".

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: iftop
       iftop_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: iftop
       iftop_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  iftop_state
    Specify predetermined 'iftop_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
